<body>
    <h1>Test Harness - Design Specification (Full vision)</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"cf2b7597ceb8" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification=
(Fullvision)-TestHarness=E2=80=94DesignSpecification">TestHarness =E2=80=94=
 Design Specification</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"4bf1d7297899" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-1.Purpose">1. Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"fb88be72434d">The core job of <code>TestHarness</code> is to=
 answer:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"bc594b3b-e08f-4652-83d5-bc90cc27a8d3">
<p local-id=3D"da3d2676e1d7">"Given this artefact (and optionally a propose=
d change), what's the proof structure around it?"</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"e7f57b0afdde">It is not just "which tests exist." It is a fu=
ll verification map that tells an agent or developer what's covered, what's=
 not, what guarantees are in place, and what the minimum set of tests to ru=
n for confidence.<br><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1203978977" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1203978977" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"4311d91630dca91c518a4c82359ce683376d58=
bb6226a8b759baf23818de07b7" width=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=
=3D"expand-control-text">AGENT USAGE SCENARIOS (User Stories)</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1203978977" class=3D"expand-content">
<h2 local-id=3D"c81b0e5f4b04" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-QueryLevels">Query Levels</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0cd6b6218424">We could have three progressive levels of deta=
il. An agent chooses the level appropriate for its current task, avoiding u=
nnecessary data transfer and processing.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"68cfaa1c-c7fe-433d-92dd-68d=
2d067dbc7" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"941fec44-a6d9-4035-9b64-22d29f05b695">
<th data-local-id=3D"0ccce968-cee1-4067-9bc4-d0c39a6fb525" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a49f07949807">Level</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"4596c1a2-2b16-46c6-a7fd-a456d70805aa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"3e094f7256bd">Primitive</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"274d6c75-7504-4209-bb94-5f44b055d7c2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a7f5645044e1">Returns</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"c297b58c-da85-4271-a1ba-6a943bbdd602" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c697abbb93f6">Use when</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"664e7d4c-7dca-4466-ace0-47f5fa1824ea">
<td data-local-id=3D"1e0a5327-6cf1-4665-aa91-51cf561b50d2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4253bfa34cfd"><strong>Summary</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9a22dd78-3221-4869-9945-77b83db2515e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ea916d57f3e0"><code>-&gt; tests().summary()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2ce78ed0-046c-478b-870e-2bdf70611985" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"314f77f6396e"><code>verification_level</code>, test counts b=
y classification, coverage percentages</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"71d9bced-b967-4462-a3b6-d9108ecd6084" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3a31b82dddfb">Quick triage =E2=80=94 "should I worry about t=
esting here?"</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"050b57ef-ba93-4755-978b-6cfa96390846">
<td data-local-id=3D"c72e769c-f07c-4e2e-9169-71f84db94af6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d98d460f0f38"><strong>Test list</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"78a48cf2-ae2b-420e-875b-e0034537a869" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b159a88ad499"><code>-&gt; tests()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4ac015a4-444c-4a17-8db7-880460aca2fa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a105d5b33376">Covering tests with classification, strength, =
confidence, pass/fail status + summary</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e93afa3a-70b8-46c9-a214-51454ae15320" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2e8f5a6855d">Planning =E2=80=94 "what tests exist, what's p=
assing, what's relevant?"</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c512b79b-c48f-41ed-ae01-ded682f2b4ea">
<td data-local-id=3D"e4eee409-e931-4c53-adb7-c2272e0dbcf7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"03c79cc16b13"><strong>Full coverage</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"774a5216-04be-4cb6-9c12-86590c104e60" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"729c98f52007"><code>-&gt; coverage()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"cc0aab4a-0cf3-4890-a393-33544894db93" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"351e9d093b52">Per-branch covered/uncovered detail with cover=
ing test IDs</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4e5f65ee-fcd8-4e0e-aec9-b83fdc5933e3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bf3a84ab6688">Deep analysis =E2=80=94 "exactly which code pa=
ths are untested?"</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"0cd415425619">Each level builds on the previous. An agent ca=
n start with summary, decide it needs more, and drill down , or go straight=
 to the level it needs.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c6c29332-c701-4f40-a58b-d3a93157af76">
<h2 local-id=3D"06371a125e57" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario1:Pre-changesafetyassessment">Scenario 1: Pre-change safety as=
sessment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bb912588570e"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Refactor <code>U=
serRepository.findById</code> to use a cache layer"</p>
<p local-id=3D"e4999a06bd3d"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "Is this ar=
tefact well-tested enough that I can refactor confidently?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"bdc9c4d93f5b"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"findById")
  -&gt; tests().summary()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"19ea06ba7604"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "verification_level": "well_tested",
  "total_covering_tests": 3,
  "unit_count": 2,
  "integration_count": 1,
  "e2e_count": 0,
  "branch_coverage_pct": 85,
  "untested_branch_count": 1
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"476cd99860a5"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> Well tested =
with 85% branch coverage. Safe to refactor. But there's 1 untested branch. =
I should be careful around it or investigate further.</p>
<p local-id=3D"65c3d68eeb53"><strong>Decision:</strong> Proceed with refact=
oring. Optionally drill into <code>-&gt; coverage()</code> to find the unte=
sted branch before starting.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9cb75dc6-b0f4-4669-bdff-9b585339efb3">
<h2 local-id=3D"9ca40666d756" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario2:Understandingwhattestsexistbeforemakingachange">Scenario 2: =
Understanding what tests exist before making a change</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a8320fce41f5"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Add soft-delete =
capability to UserRepository"</p>
<p local-id=3D"96a1c39918a8"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "What tests=
 cover the artefacts I'm about to modify? Are they passing? What type are t=
hey?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"e88985e2c531"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"findById")
  -&gt; tests()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d27d730db166"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "covering_tests": [
    {
      "test_name": "should find user by id",
      "suite_name": "UserRepository",
      "classification": "unit",
      "strength": 0.92,
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "last_run": { "status": "pass", "duration_ms": 8 }
    },
    {
      "test_name": "should return null for missing user",
      "suite_name": "UserRepository",
      "classification": "unit",
      "strength": 0.88,
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "last_run": { "status": "pass", "duration_ms": 6 }
    },
    {
      "test_name": "full user creation and retrieval flow",
      "suite_name": "UserService integration",
      "classification": "integration",
      "strength": 0.15,
      "confidence": 0.90,
      "last_run": { "status": "pass", "duration_ms": 340 }
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "verification_level": "well_tested",
    "total_covering_tests": 3,
    "unit_count": 2,
    "integration_count": 1,
    "untested_branch_count": 1
  }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"76765eb2e19e">Note:<br><strong>Confidence (0.0=E2=80=931.0):=
</strong> How sure are we this test covers this artefact. <br>
High =3D coverage-verified, low =3D static linkage only.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2322a0e348c2"><strong>Strength (0.0=E2=80=931.0):</strong> H=
ow focused this test is on this specific artefact. <br>
High =3D few artefacts covered (focused unit test), low =3D many artefacts =
covered (broad e2e test). Formula something like <code>1 / fan_out * classi=
fication_weight</code><br><br><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> Two strong =
unit tests directly verify <code>findById</code>. One weaker integration te=
st passes through it. All passing. I know which tests to watch when I modif=
y this function. If I change the return type to filter soft-deleted users, =
the "should find user by id" test will likely need updating, and the "shoul=
d return null for missing user" test validates a path I should preserve.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"ec9bb3dfd721"><strong>Decision:</strong> Modify <code>findBy=
Id</code>, update the 2 unit tests to account for soft-delete filtering, le=
ave the integration test alone.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"1cd1c5c8-777e-4c06-81f4-727e0af97c54">
<h2 local-id=3D"b0e177f4dbce" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario3:Findinguntestedcodepathsbeforefixingabug">Scenario 3: Findin=
g untested code paths before fixing a bug</h2>
<p local-id=3D"88d7943e6c2f"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Users report a 5=
00 error when email is null in createUser"</p>
<p local-id=3D"40de0dc9e1a8"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "Is the nul=
l-email path tested? Which exact branches are uncovered?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"e28649974ed0"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"createUser")
  -&gt; coverage()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"ba687f394f81"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "line_coverage_pct": 78.5,
  "branch_coverage_pct": 60.0,
  "branches": [
    { "line": 15, "description": "if (email !=3D=3D null)", "covered": true=
, "covering_test_ids": ["t1", "t2"] },
    { "line": 15, "description": "else: email is null", "covered": false, "=
covering_test_ids": [] },
    { "line": 22, "description": "if (user.isActive)", "covered": true, "co=
vering_test_ids": ["t1"] },
    { "line": 22, "description": "else: user inactive", "covered": false, "=
covering_test_ids": [] },
    { "line": 30, "description": "try block", "covered": true, "covering_te=
st_ids": ["t1", "t2"] }
  ]
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"c418d150f1fd"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> The null-ema=
il branch on line 15 is exactly the uncovered path causing the bug. No test=
 exercises this path, which explains how the bug shipped. The inactive-user=
 branch on line 22 is also untested =E2=80=94 potential second bug hiding t=
here.</p>
<p local-id=3D"44af094bbe3f"><strong>Decision:</strong> Fix the null-email =
handling, write a test specifically for that branch, and flag the untested =
inactive-user branch as a follow-up risk.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9be86e06-7c4f-4d7b-a761-a2b39a396975">
<h2 local-id=3D"f01feef1efc1" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario4:Identifyingpre-existingtestfailures">Scenario 4: Identifying=
 pre-existing test failures</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0e73958acf97"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Implement input =
validation for OrderService.createOrder"</p>
<p local-id=3D"e3836bad672c"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "Are any ex=
isting tests already failing? I need to know what's broken before I start, =
so I don't get blamed for pre-existing failures."</p>
<p local-id=3D"a6fc0538dd87"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"createOrder")
  -&gt; tests()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"8a7842d88532"><strong>Response includes:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "covering_tests": [
    {
      "test_name": "should create order with valid items",
      "classification": "unit",
      "strength": 0.90,
      "last_run": { "status": "pass", "duration_ms": 15 }
    },
    {
      "test_name": "should reject duplicate order ids",
      "classification": "unit",
      "strength": 0.85,
      "last_run": { "status": "fail", "duration_ms": 22 }
    }
  ]
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"3f91a2755959"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> "should reje=
ct duplicate order ids" is already failing. This is a pre-existing failure =
=E2=80=94 not something I introduced. I should note this in my commit messa=
ge and not spend time debugging it unless it's related to my change.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8b07e0432aa3"><strong>Decision:</strong> Proceed with valida=
tion implementation. Document the pre-existing failure. Focus on ensuring m=
y new tests pass.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c24148d8-4f97-4162-9f93-844e456b821e">
<h2 local-id=3D"ce34fe735faa" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario6:Assessinganunfamiliarartefact">Scenario 6: Assessing an unfa=
miliar artefact</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3c91606a6549"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Optimize the per=
formance of <code>PaymentGateway.processRefund</code>"</p>
<p local-id=3D"8d4f1176bead"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "I've never=
 seen this code before. What's the testing situation?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"b129a0d669fa"><strong>Query (start with summary):</strong></=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"processRefund")
  -&gt; tests().summary()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"e01bfd6a32f5"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "verification_level": "untested",
  "total_covering_tests": 0
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"313adf3ba1af"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> Zero tests. =
This is a high-risk artefact to modify =E2=80=94 any change could break beh=
aviour with no safety net.</p>
<p local-id=3D"33c5f4388f0c"><strong>Decision:</strong> Before optimizing, =
write characterization tests that document current behaviour. Then optimize=
 with the tests as a regression guard.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"de1a1c48-843f-4681-ba41-fc10baf27662">
<h2 local-id=3D"b311299866c7" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario7:PRreview=E2=80=94isthischangeadequatelytested?">Scenario 7: =
PR review =E2=80=94 is this change adequately tested?</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a9032ef0218f"><strong>Agent task:</strong> Reviewing a PR th=
at modifies <code>AuthService.validateToken</code></p>
<p local-id=3D"5182652c97ca"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "Does the c=
hanged artefact have adequate test coverage?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"b401ec767057"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"feature/oauth")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"validateToken")
  -&gt; tests().summary()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"fc21f062d734"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "verification_level": "partially_tested",
  "total_covering_tests": 1,
  "unit_count": 0,
  "integration_count": 1,
  "e2e_count": 0,
  "branch_coverage_pct": 35,
  "untested_branch_count": 4
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"9abda801d547"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> Only 1 integ=
ration test, no unit tests, 35% branch coverage with 4 untested branches. T=
his is a security-sensitive artefact (authentication) with weak verificatio=
n.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c8cb53344152"><strong>Decision:</strong> Flag in PR review: =
"This change modifies <code>validateToken</code> which has only 35% branch =
coverage and no unit tests. 4 branches are untested. Recommend adding focus=
ed unit tests before merging, especially for a security-sensitive path."</p=
>
<hr local-id=3D"937ee3d8-986f-4930-8abd-f8ef65ce5e17">
<h2 local-id=3D"b8e8b5d23752" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario8:Red-phaseTDD=E2=80=94writingtestsfirst">Scenario 8: Red-phas=
e TDD =E2=80=94 writing tests first</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e9b321701b55"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Add input valida=
tion to OrderService.createOrder =E2=80=94 reject orders with negative quan=
tities"</p>
<p local-id=3D"002d3ffde9e2"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "What tests=
 already exist, and what patterns do they follow?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"706f5758210c"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"createOrder")
  -&gt; tests()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"f2f1183a20c9"><strong>Agent examines:</strong> The existing =
test names, their structure, which suite they belong to. Sees that existing=
 tests follow the pattern <code>should [verb] [condition]</code> inside a <=
code>describe('OrderService')</code> suite.</p>
<p local-id=3D"021b51cc8a9e"><strong>Decision:</strong> Write a new test fo=
llowing the same pattern: <code>it('should reject orders with negative quan=
tities')</code>. The test fails (red phase). Then implement the validation =
to make it pass (green phase). The test harness data informed the testing c=
onventions in use.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a54e7267-c2ad-46e9-8e01-bd557f7d9eb6">
<h2 local-id=3D"69e2a410fc3b" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario9:Cross-cuttingartefact=E2=80=94managingnoise">Scenario 9: Cro=
ss-cutting artefact =E2=80=94 managing noise</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ddc83d312eef"><strong>Agent task:</strong> Modifying <code>L=
ogger.log</code> to add structured logging</p>
<p local-id=3D"ae34b4c337ae"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "What tests=
 cover the logger?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"6f05debf19ca"><strong>Query (start with summary):</strong></=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"log")
  -&gt; tests().summary()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"a48e7a35e23a"><strong>Response:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "verification_level": "well_tested",
  "total_covering_tests": 147,
  "unit_count": 3,
  "integration_count": 28,
  "e2e_count": 116,
  "branch_coverage_pct": 100
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"bdee8435d33d"><strong>Agent reasoning:</strong> 147 tests is=
 noise. But the summary tells me: 3 unit tests directly target the logger (=
high strength), while 144 other tests merely pass through it. I only care a=
bout the 3 direct tests.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9936611e22c4"><strong>Query (drill down, filtered):</strong>=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"log")
  -&gt; tests(classification:"unit")
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"dffeb9e1f870"><strong>Response:</strong> 3 focused unit test=
s for the logger. These are the tests that will break if I change the loggi=
ng interface.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dff6095f3d8c"><strong>Decision:</strong> Focus on the 3 unit=
 tests. The 144 other tests won't break unless I change the logger's extern=
al API, which I'm not doing.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"71994d8c-8906-4142-8ab3-1134b3f455cd">
<h2 local-id=3D"9856f49ccbdd" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Scenario10:Agentdecideswhethertowritenewtests">Scenario 10: Agent deci=
des whether to write new tests</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f714a90f61c1"><strong>Agent task:</strong> "Add email format=
 validation to UserService.createUser"</p>
<p local-id=3D"e9798ee354ff"><strong>Agent's question:</strong> "Is the are=
a I'm changing well-tested, or do I need to write tests as part of this cha=
nge?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"bb0e742bc7f0"><strong>Query:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">repo("m=
yapp") -&gt; asOf(ref:"main")
  -&gt; artefacts(name:"createUser")
  -&gt; tests().summary()
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"7d2507953f9d"><strong>If </strong><code>verification_level: =
well_tested</code><strong>:</strong> Agent adds the validation logic and re=
lies on existing tests to catch regressions. May add one targeted test for =
the new validation path.</p>
<p local-id=3D"4d7fd2ec362e"><strong>If </strong><code>verification_level: =
untested</code><strong>:</strong> Agent writes comprehensive tests first =
=E2=80=94 both for existing behaviour (characterization tests) and for the =
new validation =E2=80=94 before making any changes.</p>
<p local-id=3D"eab2d7e4c956"><strong>If </strong><code>verification_level: =
partially_tested</code><strong>:</strong> Agent checks <code>-&gt; coverage=
()</code> to see which specific branches are untested, writes tests for the=
 gaps that overlap with the change area, then implements.</p>
<p local-id=3D"021c4a2e984f"><strong>The </strong><code>verification_level<=
/code><strong> directly determines the agent's strategy.</strong> This is t=
he single most important signal for agent planning.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"b3544022-43b6-4896-a909-765bdcdf3934">
<h2 local-id=3D"47fbc21a227d" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Summary:QueryLevelbyTask">Summary: Query Level by Task</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"88b3cf2c-e09c-4e71-b9ff-787=
49918077d" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"82653faf-67cd-4be1-818f-4db7e208c7cb">
<th data-local-id=3D"0bb32ba1-3a2c-4653-b6a3-3500a3f96d87" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"d1e7dbbc8301">Agent task</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"5ceb0639-af5c-4a3e-8a73-73171003d702" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e8f5a8412a37">Recommended query level</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"b794a729-31f2-4749-9465-c114cf76ddda" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"93578fca7d21">Why</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"763b0b97-cd4c-464e-b194-06e7858e33c2">
<td data-local-id=3D"0ce659a7-5710-4b8d-a342-bd023a3596c3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d1c8a63042d0">Quick triage / "should I worry?"</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c1d1d516-5923-41c3-8d50-1966c0c6edf1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a274d2972939"><code>tests().summary()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d3a5b7a9-2f9f-4306-8656-708fdcd53bbb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"874119d96530">One number tells the agent whether to proceed =
or investigate</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b903e365-5f48-4036-91dc-a9648a109779">
<td data-local-id=3D"f4ece950-589e-4783-abc0-9575d620e466" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"99652061c0aa">Planning a change</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f3ca16a5-0285-4532-b3c8-29ba4629c584" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3f7c41ba8e5a"><code>tests()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c1d47732-3837-4583-8bb0-bafd11edc5ac" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4148b3b7dd8a">Need to know what tests exist, what's passing,=
 what's strong</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3092afd0-51ac-449b-907a-80b9de1755ac">
<td data-local-id=3D"1461370c-b61f-4f87-a472-5d24356c472f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a32b5ac2af7a">Finding exact gaps for a bug fix</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fc9b856e-84ce-4339-b5d6-820df293cb3f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"842345ccaa47"><code>coverage()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aecf15e5-2bd1-4fc1-b447-7295a832fb13" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7df9c3521ebd">Need per-branch detail to locate the untested =
path</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ef070e10-56fb-4ba9-bdfb-880144e68433">
<td data-local-id=3D"a50956ba-cb6b-4d8e-a26f-28eaf59b149f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3b4b21f11024">Choosing which tests to run</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"18c3c8ad-01f0-4baa-b2ea-d8e0c871c095" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2bc607b9262a"><code>tests()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d5226692-0ec4-47fe-b210-3167c60790df" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2c7c62ef916">Need test names, paths, classification for pri=
oritization</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2b1daa1b-f8b7-4ee0-a1cc-e23d918c5e65">
<td data-local-id=3D"2597042c-3d29-4d4e-ab2a-ce93c3df893c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8f3430c1e943">PR review</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9635129e-fc8d-449a-b29a-10dff98807c5" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3c911134cbb1"><code>tests().summary()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"39eb6ef8-3de8-45be-9608-f7d328cd9d65" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1938abf7919e">Quick assessment of coverage adequacy</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"434cab0a-de36-4ab6-93a2-503b3a314192">
<td data-local-id=3D"4392eb44-8de0-4e40-bbd9-89c06f67aa0b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"07525e45fcb5">Writing new tests (TDD)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"bbe06162-6229-46cc-8c7b-7ece6b200a66" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c5948e40dff9"><code>tests()</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4f3e789e-1844-43a5-94a7-15cbcd990af3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"445447c13ed9">Need existing test patterns and conventions</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"03a59e7c-1e87-4f63-a7ec-2c187799fa3c">
<td data-local-id=3D"e5cff5a4-4564-4c5b-8168-c983bc0a5091" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"414e2d008d5f">Cross-cutting artefact</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9a52485e-c540-4665-8167-ec59915bb1de" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"befcae950d38"><code>tests().summary()</code> then <code>test=
s(classification:"unit")</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"45b6f196-12e4-4888-94bb-bc367da9ee49" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a2dc5e48ef09">Summary reveals noise, filter extracts signal<=
/p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"d1ff40508a97" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-2.FullCapabilityScope">2. Full Capability Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6b4de68bd055"><code>getTestHarness</code> should return: (<a=
 href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/431194113/Co=
debase+Intelligence+Plane+Ranked+Context+Tools+for+Coding+Agents#5.-getTest=
Harness-(Verification-Map)" data-linked-resource-id=3D"431194113" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"4" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">source</a>)</p=
>
<div id=3D"expander-429923949" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-429923949" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"4311d91630dca91c518a4c82359ce683376d58=
bb6226a8b759baf23818de07b7" width=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=
=3D"expand-control-text">1. Unit/integration/e2e tests covering the artefac=
t</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-429923949" class=3D"expand-content">
<p local-id=3D"1ad5a345b88e">This bullet answers: "What tests exist around =
this artefact, and what kind of tests are they?"</p>
<p local-id=3D"3485e707fd56">It decomposes into three distinct subproblems:=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"792b7faa-cde2-4dce-b666-370e5687c431">
<li local-id=3D"ab718d16-d6cc-4150-a27e-be160c4e47ad">
<p local-id=3D"109e635e1e9d"><strong>Part A =E2=80=94 Test-to-artefact link=
age</strong>: Which tests reference or exercise this artefact?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a034f86-d7a7-46f6-805c-548afeefcf43">
<p local-id=3D"699915b74eac"><strong>Part B =E2=80=94 Cross-cutting artefac=
t handling</strong>: How do we avoid flooding results when an artefact is t=
ouched by everything?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6c63e84b-e768-4d15-98bf-b755daeeace2">
<p local-id=3D"ace8375bf8ad"><strong>Part C =E2=80=94 Test classification</=
strong>: Is a given test a unit test, integration test, or e2e test?</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e1d03437d7fc">Parts A and B are <strong>linkage problems</st=
rong> (what's connected and how to manage signal-to-noise). Part C is a <st=
rong>labelling problem</strong> (what kind of thing is it). They have diffe=
rent failure modes and different solution spaces.</p>
<p local-id=3D"75e974c58d33"></p>
<hr local-id=3D"8e13be39f50c">
<p local-id=3D"1ec571e7c185"><strong>Part A: Test-to-artefact linkage</stro=
ng></p>
<p local-id=3D"a0bb52f46d64"><strong>Problem</strong>: Given a production a=
rtefact, determine which test scenarios exercise it.<br><br>
The fundamental challenge is indirection. A test might reach an artefact th=
rough direct import and call (easy to detect), or through factory functions=
, dependency injection, dynamic dispatch, event emitters, or runtime config=
uration (hard to detect statically). Any linkage strategy must handle the e=
asy cases reliably and degrade gracefully on the hard cases.<br><br></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"40a76a05eb77" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Recommendedapproach:Staticanalysis(Tree-sitter)">Recommended approach:=
 Static analysis (Tree-sitter)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"fe62268053b7">Parse test files to discover test-specific art=
efacts (test suites and test scenarios) and resolve which production artefa=
cts they reference via import and call-site analysis. This creates <code>te=
st_scenario -&gt; production_artefact</code> edges stored in the graph.<br>=
<br>
Reuses the Tree-sitter parsing infrastructure built for <code>getBlastRadiu=
s</code>. The investment in the static analysis pipeline pays off twice.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"94c5909c2a97"></p>
<p local-id=3D"076caef96ed9"><strong>On transitive calls</strong>: If test =
scenario A calls production function <code>createUser</code>, and <code>cre=
ateUser</code> internally calls <code>validateEmail</code> and <code>hashPa=
ssword</code>, the transitive call chain means the test is indirectly exerc=
ising those artefacts too. The static analysis can follow this via the exis=
ting dependency graph from <code>getBlastRadius</code>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f788cee36d0e">Design choice: create edges for direct calls o=
nly, or include transitive?</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ad81620b-ea66-4a16-9b65-4e5=
1810a3c70" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a8d10138-370f-4dc7-8a6d-5bdb64f0c385">
<th data-local-id=3D"edc3c7a2-ffa4-4958-b171-09c657875ab7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9dac4e8016a7">Approach</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"697eee21-7fce-45e3-a8ba-58887db41b11" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"97c0e8f70168">Precision</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"ecec3e92-fda1-4ca5-b638-e70429dbe667" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ddaa944e30ea">Completeness</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"3db04955-f7e6-4ed0-82cf-d4ce60ad2238" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"534935fd5bec">Noise</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"994f9d69-3c4c-479e-ae7c-73ec5cc36f6a">
<td data-local-id=3D"5175960b-b8a0-4129-929d-98f340cc9f55" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"364936bcd9aa">Direct-only</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1b39cf2a-78b7-45dd-91a9-bf2149eb3c69" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8f5708ad2770">High</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"acf6f872-cd8b-4766-a6cb-322d1f4e600b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de120e2c2770">Lower (misses transitive)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"76ad86e5-d9df-4bd2-888b-05b1c4a7de40" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2db13afefbcf">Low</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5a6e66c1-4749-4e00-9fe6-a05a0b1e1ac4">
<td data-local-id=3D"fc734446-5db4-411a-9eea-dac415ef7dbc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c50103149be">Transitive</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e53d0cc0-f3ed-4418-847e-0a23cf433412" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c376f3b0d3d6">Lower</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ff83b29b-90fa-4515-bc9a-9111be1ef77f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1c23ba0b34b6">High</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4613a494-312f-4b92-a3d1-29ba234df301" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"47760cfde8ae">High (edges to barely-touched artefacts)</p></=
td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"e4b866243e7c">Pragmatic approach: <strong>static linkage cap=
tures direct calls only, coverage data captures actual execution depth (inc=
luding transitive).</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"bbeab4944888"></p>
<p local-id=3D"adcd03e8453a"><strong><u>Strengths</u></strong>: Available a=
t commit time, costs nothing beyond parsing. Handles the majority of cases =
(direct imports and calls) reliably.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fd7431e8fa81"><strong><u>Limitations</u></strong>: Tells you=
 what a test <em>reaches for</em>, not what it <em>exercises</em>. Misses a=
rtefacts reached through indirection patterns (DI containers, factories, dy=
namic dispatch, event-driven architectures). Direct-only linkage may miss a=
rtefacts exercised transitively.<br></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"90f10c00f039" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Alternativeapproaches"><br><strong>Alternative approaches</strong></h2=
>
<p local-id=3D"fc1d79af23b0"></p>
<p local-id=3D"f1c5e64388c6"><strong>Naming convention heuristics</strong> =
Fuzzy string matching between test suite/scenario names and production arte=
fact names. <code>UserRepository.test.ts</code> almost certainly tests <cod=
e>UserRepository.ts</code>. <code>describe('findById')</code> almost certai=
nly tests <code>findById</code>. Nearly zero implementation cost, high prec=
ision when conventions are followed, fails silently when they don't. Best u=
sed as a supplementary signal that raises confidence on existing static lin=
ks rather than a standalone method.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5edc1030ff9f"><strong>Embedding-based semantic similarity</s=
trong> Embed test code and production code into a shared vector space (e.g.=
, Qodo-Embed-1-1.5B for local deployment). Find tests semantically close to=
 a given artefact even without a static import trail. Catches indirection p=
atterns that static analysis misses: the test <em>talks about the same conc=
epts</em> (same variable names, domain language, error conditions) even if =
there's no syntactic link. Weakness is precision: semantic closeness doesn'=
t guarantee execution. Best used as a <strong>discovery layer for candidate=
 links</strong> when static analysis finds nothing, with candidates carryin=
g lower confidence scores.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3dbd4a67ab61"><strong>Dynamic instrumentation / runtime trac=
ing</strong> Instrument the test runner to record which production function=
s were called during each test scenario's execution, with call stacks. Capt=
ures dynamic dispatch, DI, runtime configuration, and any indirection patte=
rn that defeats static resolution. Gives structured caller/callee relations=
hips per test, not just flat line hits. Requires framework-specific instrum=
entation (Node.js <code>--loader</code> hooks for TS, compile-time instrume=
ntation for Rust). Only available after execution. Higher engineering cost =
than static analysis, but would make the transitive linkage question largel=
y moot. Clean upgrade path for post-MVP.</p>
<p local-id=3D"4b8614d31ee6"></p>
<p local-id=3D"5f38cf7158bc"><strong>Historical co-change analysis (git-bas=
ed)</strong> Mine git history for co-change patterns: if <code>findById</co=
de> and <code>findById.test.ts</code> are modified in the same commits repe=
atedly, that's strong evidence of a testing relationship. Captures links th=
at no code analysis can see, reflecting developer intent over time. Degrade=
s for new code (no history), noisy for large commits. Best used as backgrou=
nd enrichment that adjusts confidence scores on existing links.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ce52e3a9fbc5"></p>
<p local-id=3D"940286a22576"><strong>LLM-based linkage inference</strong> U=
se an LLM to examine a test's code and infer which production artefacts it =
verifies. Can understand intent through builder patterns, mock setups, HTTP=
 test clients, and other indirection that defeats all other methods. Cost/l=
atency managed by running as offline enrichment (post-commit batch, not que=
ry-time). Best reserved for ambiguous cases where static + embedding method=
s produce sparse or uncertain results.</p>
<p local-id=3D"68d08be4270f"></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"6990a4a93725" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Recommendedlayeredresolution">Recommended layered resolution</h3>
