nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7ed0256c323a">Question</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"67102e7e-3233-48ca-9920-f94674c05dc2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9f2bd9efb353">Notes</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4aabb957-4c70-4a5a-8460-bfb37ee560ca">
<td data-local-id=3D"bd19a16a-4fe5-4296-8ef8-af9b4ab777b2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"30ccf92a8eed">D1</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"264af052-53af-424e-9a8b-e823238aed6f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cb4abde6d281">Coverage-derived classification thresholds</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3fdff4e7-3d44-4b9a-8469-3e3de3f642cf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"484b647137bd">What artefact fan-out values define unit vs in=
tegration vs e2e? Requires empirical tuning against real codebases.</p></td=
>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bd875121-02fe-471e-a11c-0ab167a01706">
<td data-local-id=3D"e6918d87-0b8a-468a-acce-7dd8093e3657" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"da213c6ab742">D2</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5c885060-a6b8-4c5f-8f36-4762efe22eca" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"171dc611cd3d"><code>verification_level</code> thresholds</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"068cad36-9862-40da-a398-173d9e0e33ba" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a5922796e201">What coverage/test counts define well_tested v=
s partially_tested vs untested? Requires empirical tuning.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b8abfcc1-50ed-49b1-bf08-781ae2e567d6">
<td data-local-id=3D"77e00723-ac0d-4534-bd53-fd1c30c934ef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d57bc19d4e67">D3</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b44b7bbe-b303-48f8-931c-a4026b8480be" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ed68a78d785f">Transport/consumption pattern</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6cde2e7c-207c-4f7a-a0ec-31796fc82cea" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9f75880db6f9">How agents invoke DevQL queries =E2=80=94 MCP =
server, direct CLI invocation, or both. Response shape is the same regardle=
ss.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"06ee0c2bba62"><br></p>
<p local-id=3D"0c9dd9fd90e2"></p>
<hr local-id=3D"b769f2d9300e">
<h2 local-id=3D"4e7f793a6620" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-5.Deferred(PostBullets1&amp;2)">5. Deferred (Post Bullets 1 &amp; 2)</=
h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"8ab44d3d8adb" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-5.1Bullet3=E2=80=94AssertionsandBehaviouralGuarantees">5.1 Bullet 3 =
=E2=80=94 Assertions and Behavioural Guarantees</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a4f3fb2736f0" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Ranges from str=
aightforward (extracting <code>expect</code>/<code>assert</code> statements=
 and associating them with artefacts) to ambitious (summarizing what a test=
 <em>proves</em> in domain terms, e.g., "this test guarantees idempotency")=
. MVP landing point on that spectrum TBD. Likely starts with assertion extr=
action via static analysis and adds LLM-enriched summaries later.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b2481e55f89c" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-5.2Bullets4&amp;5=E2=80=94IntelligenceLayer(Post-MVPR&amp;D)">5.2 Bull=
ets 4 &amp; 5 =E2=80=94 Intelligence Layer (Post-MVP R&amp;D)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5da8bee1bb59" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Bullet =
4: Required fixtures/factories/mocks for fast extension</strong> <strong>Bu=
llet 5: Recommended minimal validation suite for a proposed change</strong>=
</p>
<p local-id=3D"d4398c322806" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">These are not d=
ata retrieval problems =E2=80=94 they are recommendation/intelligence probl=
ems. The system must reason about test patterns and propose actionable guid=
ance. Several approaches are worth exploring, potentially in combination.</=
p>
<h4 local-id=3D"3f06b74ce4d7" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"TestHarn=
ess-DesignSpecification(Fullvision)-ApproachA:Embedding-basedpatternmatchin=
g">Approach A: Embedding-based pattern matching</h4>
<p local-id=3D"43fb3d48d277" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Generate embedd=
ings for test setup patterns (fixtures, factories, mocks) across the codeba=
se. When an agent needs to extend testing for an artefact, retrieve the mos=
t similar existing test setups via nearest-neighbour search. This is relati=
vely cheap, runs locally against pgvector, and leverages the semantic clone=
 infrastructure already planned for the platform.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2af7a4ec075b" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Strengt=
hs:</strong> Low latency, no external API calls, reuses existing embedding =
pipeline. <strong>Limitations:</strong> Can only recommend patterns that al=
ready exist in the codebase. Cannot reason about <em>why</em> a particular =
setup is needed.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"00de88f542db" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"TestHarn=
ess-DesignSpecification(Fullvision)-ApproachB:LocalLLMinference">Approach B=
: Local LLM inference</h4>
<p local-id=3D"25ccf23fdbca" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Use a local mod=
el (e.g., a small code-specialised model running on the developer's machine=
) to analyse the artefact, its test harness data (from bullets 1 &amp; 2), =
and its blast radius to generate fixture/mock recommendations and minimal v=
alidation suites.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e594e7fb6d4b" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Strengt=
hs:</strong> No external API dependency, keeps data local, can reason about=
 context. <strong>Limitations:</strong> Quality depends on model capability=
, compute cost on developer machine, model management complexity.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"51c8dd19af97" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"TestHarn=
ess-DesignSpecification(Fullvision)-ApproachC:PaidLLMinference(API-based)">=
Approach C: Paid LLM inference (API-based)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"912d712bd948" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Send the artefa=
ct context, test harness data, and blast radius to a capable hosted model (=
e.g., Claude, GPT) to generate recommendations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"854c4cf36a6d" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Strengt=
hs:</strong> Highest reasoning quality, can synthesize complex recommendati=
ons. <strong>Limitations:</strong> Latency, cost per query, data leaves the=
 local environment, dependency on external service.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"eb95e3c8ea08" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"TestHarn=
ess-DesignSpecification(Fullvision)-ApproachD:Rule-basedheuristicsfromcover=
agedata">Approach D: Rule-based heuristics from coverage data</h4>
<p local-id=3D"a9918b418501" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">For bullet 5 sp=
ecifically, the minimal validation suite could be derived without any LLM i=
nvolvement: select tests that cover the changed artefact, prioritize by str=
ength score and classification (unit first, then integration, then e2e), an=
d flag untested branches as requiring new tests. This is a deterministic al=
gorithm operating on the data foundation from bullets 1 &amp; 2.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dd89a119c941" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Strengt=
hs:</strong> Fast, deterministic, no model dependency, explainable. <strong=
>Limitations:</strong> Cannot reason about <em>what kind</em> of test to wr=
ite, only <em>which existing tests to run</em>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"24694b0e0270" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-5.3Heuristic-BasedTestClassification(Option2)">5.3 Heuristic-Based Tes=
t Classification (Option 2)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c9c820ceb205">May revisit for high-confidence patterns in TS=
 and Rust. Not in MVP scope.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f5a09498-9072-4d64-8b4d-712a062d31ed">
<h2 local-id=3D"45dade9af800" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-AppendixA:Commit-AddressableStorageExplained">Appendix A: Commit-Addre=
ssable Storage Explained</h2>
<p local-id=3D"78da86210ebc"><strong>The core problem:</strong> Code is a m=
oving target. A branch name like <code>main</code> or <code>feature/auth</c=
ode> points to a different commit every time someone pushes. If you store a=
 fact like "UserRepository.findById has 85% branch coverage" and you attach=
 that to <code>main</code>, it becomes meaningless the moment <code>main</c=
ode> moves forward. Which version of <code>main</code>? The one from today?=
 Yesterday? Before or after the rebase?</p>
<p local-id=3D"14373ee73a8c"><strong>The solution: store everything against=
 commit SHAs.</strong> A commit SHA is immutable =E2=80=94 it's a unique fi=
ngerprint of a specific state of the code. It never changes, it never moves=
. So when you store "UserRepository.findById has 85% branch coverage at com=
mit <code>a1b2c3d</code>", that fact is permanently true. It doesn't decay =
or become ambiguous.</p>
<p local-id=3D"de3312921bee"><strong>But people think in branches, not SHAs=
.</strong> A developer asks "what's the coverage on <code>main</code>?" not=
 "what's the coverage at <code>a1b2c3d</code>?" So at query time, the syste=
m resolves the ref to its current commit: <code>main</code> =E2=86=92 <code=
>a1b2c3d</code> =E2=86=92 look up facts stored against <code>a1b2c3d</code>=
. The ref is just a pointer; the data lives on the commit.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a8684e37e5d5"><strong>Historical ref movement</strong> takes=
 this one step further. You don't just track where <code>main</code> points=
 <em>now</em> =E2=80=94 you track where it pointed at every moment in the p=
ast. So if someone asks "what was the coverage on <code>main</code> last Tu=
esday at 3pm?", you look up which commit <code>main</code> pointed to at th=
at timestamp, and then retrieve the facts for that commit. That's the "as-o=
f" reproducibility. Without this history, you can only answer questions abo=
ut the present state of a branch, never the past.</p>
<p local-id=3D"60d986adda81"><strong>No branch-only facts without commit li=
nkage</strong> is the discipline that makes all of this work. It means you =
never store something like "this test passed on <code>feature/auth</code>" =
without also recording the commit SHA. If you did, and that branch gets reb=
ased or force-pushed, the data becomes orphaned =E2=80=94 you can't tell wh=
at code state it referred to.</p>
<p local-id=3D"373457b03179"><strong>Concretely for </strong><code>getTestH=
arness</code><strong>:</strong> every test-to-artefact linkage, every cover=
age map, every test run outcome is stored with a <code>commit_sha</code>. W=
hen a query comes in asking about a branch, the system resolves the branch =
to its head commit and looks up data from there. When coverage data arrives=
 from CI, it's tagged with the exact commit that was tested. The result is =
that you can always trace back exactly what was true at any point in the co=
debase's history.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9fd363fa2f3d">
<h2 local-id=3D"fe8faeeaf63d" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-AppendixB:CodeEmbeddingModels=E2=80=94Research(March2026)">Appendix B:=
 Code Embedding Models =E2=80=94 Research (March 2026)</h2>
<blockquote local-id=3D"d8c5f29b-ee1d-40e1-a783-bae68396c6a7">
<p local-id=3D"10e04dbaa8f3"><strong>Note:</strong> The embedding model lan=
dscape evolves rapidly. This research reflects the state as of March 2026 a=
nd should be revalidated before implementation decisions are made. Benchmar=
k scores do not always predict real-world performance =E2=80=94 validation =
against actual TypeScript and Rust codebases is required.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 local-id=3D"a6278a32b482" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Whycode-specializedmodelsmatter">Why code-specialized models matter</h=
3>
<p local-id=3D"288f5f7ff5a0">General-purpose embedding models focus on lang=
uage patterns rather than code-specific elements like syntax, variable depe=
ndencies, control flow, and API usage. This leads to irrelevant or imprecis=
e retrieval when matching test setup patterns, fixture structures, or seman=
tically similar code artefacts. Code-specialized models are trained to unde=
rstand the functional meaning of code, not just keyword overlap.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b98429b7750d" id=3D"TestHarness-DesignSpecification(Fullvis=
ion)-Tier1:Code-SpecializedModels(purpose-builtforcoderetrieval)">Tier 1: C=
ode-Specialized Models (purpose-built for code retrieval)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"b7750704264a">These models are trained specifically on code =
corpora and optimized for code-to-code and natural-language-to-code retriev=
al.</p>
